                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-14-off78 t18180506-14-crimeloc81"></join>, and felt some person pressing my right-hand coat pocket, and saw the reflection of my handkerchief in the window - I turned round, and saw it in the prisoner's hand; he passed it to another man, who instantly walked away. I caught hold of the prisoner, and desired the crowd to hold him while I pursued the other, but no person would hold him, therefore the other got away.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I have always been honest, and am innocent.</p>
